lead_paragraph: Ireland flanker Jordi Murphy, who scored the first try in Saturday's historic triumph over New Zealand, will be sidelined for six to nine months with a knee injury, the Irish Rugby Football Union (IRFU) announced on Monday.

headline.print_headline: Ireland Flanker Murphy Out for Up to Nine Months
